# Vyntrio OS — Environment Variables (Example)

Copy to `.env` at the repository root for local development.
Do not commit real secrets.

```bash
# Application
VYNTRIO_ENV=development
VYNTRIO_LOG_LEVEL=debug

# Backend API (Phase 1+)
VYNTRIO_API_HOST=127.0.0.1
VYNTRIO_API_PORT=8080

# Frontend dev server (Phase 1+)
VYNTRIO_WEB_HOST=127.0.0.1
VYNTRIO_WEB_PORT=5173

# Database (Phase 1+ — confirm in docs/02_ARCHITECTURE.md)
# VYNTRIO_DATABASE_URL=postgres://user:pass@localhost:5432/vyntrio?sslmode=disable
```

See also:

- `docs/17_SECURITY.md` — secret handling
- `docs/21_CURSOR_REPO_SETUP.md` — bootstrap on a new machine
